🔹 STEP 1: Launch 2 EC2 Instances

Create:

Instance	Subnet
EFS-1
EFS-2	
with Amazon
Important Security Group Rule
Add:

Type	Port	Source
NFS	2049	Anywhere (0.0.0.0/0) OR VPC CIDR

Port 2049 is required for EFS.

🔹 STEP 2: Create EFS File System

Go to:

EFS → Create File System

Choose:

VPC: Default

Enable regional

Keep default performance

In Network settings:

Remove default SG

Attach your NFS security group

Click Create.

🔹 STEP 3: Connect to Both EC2 Instances

Open two PowerShell windows.

SSH into both:

ssh -i key.pem ec2-user@<public-ip>

Switch to root:

sudo su
🔹 STEP 4: Install EFS Utilities

For Amazon Linux:

yum install -y amazon-efs-utils

For Ubuntu (if used):

apt install -y amazon-efs-utils
🔹 STEP 5: Mount EFS

Go to:

EFS → Your File System → Attach

Copy the mount command.

It will look like:

sudo mount -t efs fs-xxxx:/ efs

First create mount directory:

mkdir efs

Then run mount command on BOTH instances.

🔹 STEP 6: Verify Mount

Run:

df -h

You should see something like:

fs-xxxx.efs.region.amazonaws.com:/  mounted on /efs
🔹 STEP 7: Test Shared Storage

On EFS-1:

cd /efs
touch file1
ls

Now go to EFS-2:

cd /efs
ls

✅ You will see file1
